In plano-2D apps the bottom-left corner of `.plano-container` (col 1, row 2 of the grid — under the soundline) gets a diagonal gradient that visually merges the soundline's pink with the timeline's yellow endcap.

```css
body[data-visual="nuzic"].myapp .plano-container {
  gap: 0 !important;          /* matrix must touch timeline directly       */
  position: relative;         /* anchor for absolute .plano-subdivision-label */
}

body[data-visual="nuzic"].myapp .plano-container::before {
  background: linear-gradient(
    to bottom right,
    var(--nuzic-pink) 0%,
    var(--nuzic-pink) 49.5%,
    var(--nuzic-yellow) 50.5%,
    var(--nuzic-yellow) 100%
  ) !important;
  /* Extend upward by half-cell to cover the padding-bottom of soundline-row
     (reserved for the `-0-` text translateY(50%)). */
  margin-top: calc(-1 * var(--plano-cell-height, 32px) / 2) !important;
}
```

The `::before` is created by `plano-modular.css` (it's the grid cell at col 1, row 2). We override its background to make a half-pink half-yellow diagonal. Critical: `margin-top: calc(-cellHeight/2)` covers the soundline's padding-bottom gap.

Also apply the same `margin-top` to the timeline-container to close the gap between row-0 of the matrix and the timeline:

```css
body[data-visual="nuzic"].myapp .plano-timeline-container {
  margin-top: calc(-1 * var(--plano-cell-height, 32px) / 2) !important;
}
```

