JS (en `renderGridTimeline` o equivalente, tras crear los pulse-numbers):

```javascript
const planoContainer = gridElements?.container;
if (planoContainer) {
  let subdivisionLabel = planoContainer.querySelector('.plano-subdivision-label');
  if (!subdivisionLabel) {
    subdivisionLabel = document.createElement('div');
    subdivisionLabel.className = 'plano-subdivision-label';
    planoContainer.appendChild(subdivisionLabel);
  }
  // Simple: '1/d'. Complex: 'n/d' (con n y d dinámicos).
  subdivisionLabel.textContent = `${n}/${d}`;
}
```

Fracciones simples (App32/App34): `1/d` (numerador fijo). Complejas (App33/App35): `n/d` dinámico.

Ghost-pulses are integer pulses that don't land on subdivision boundaries (only relevant when `n > 1`). The `renderGhostPulseLines` lib creates `<div class="ghost-pulse-line">` inside `.plano-matrix`. Style them as repeated dots, one per row:

```css
body[data-visual="nuzic"].myapp .ghost-pulse-line {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  bottom: calc(var(--plano-cell-height, 2rem) / 2 + 1.4rem);
  border-left: none !important;
  opacity: 1 !important;
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: 11;              /* ABOVE .plano-cell (which is opaque) */
  width: 12px;              /* room around dot, no clipping        */
  background-image: radial-gradient(
    circle 2px at 50% 50%,  /* dot at center, not corner (avoids clip) */
    rgba(67, 67, 59, 0.68) 50%,
    transparent 51%
  );
  background-size: 100% var(--plano-cell-height, 2rem);
  background-position: 0 calc(var(--plano-cell-height, 2rem) / 2);
  background-repeat: repeat-y;
  transform: translateX(-50%);
}
```

Four critical decisions:

1. `z-index: 11` — `.plano-cell` has opaque background, would otherwise cover dots.
2. `width: 12px` (not 3px) — the dot is 4px diameter; needs lateral margin to avoid being clipped by background-clip.
3. `circle 2px at 50% 50%` — center of tile, not bottom or top corner (which would be cut).
4. `background-position-y: calc(cellHeight/2)` — shifts repetition so the first dot lands at y=cellHeight (first row division), the next at 2×cellHeight, etc.

`rgba(0.68)` makes dots subdued (vs. `.pulse-boundary::before` dots which are full `--nuzic-dark`). Visual hierarchy: pulses on cells stand out more than ghost pulses.

```javascript
import { createPlayheadController } from '../../libs/plano-modular/plano-playhead.js';

playheadController = createPlayheadController(
  gridElements.matrixContainer,
  () => 0,        // getCellWidth: 0 activa modo DOM (necesario con columnSizing: 'fr')
  0,              // offset (siempre 0 para Nuzic)
  -1              // domOffset: -1 px para alinear exactamente con pulse-number x
);

// Cancelar el marginLeft: -4px que createPlayhead aplica por defecto
// (legacy de App19/App20). En Nuzic queremos el playhead exactamente
// en cell.offsetLeft.
