Usa `showValidationWarning` del módulo info-tooltip:

```javascript
import { showValidationWarning } from '../../libs/app-common/info-tooltip.js';

function commitToken(cell, rawInput) {
  const parsed = parseAndValidateToken(rawInput);

  if (!parsed) {
    showValidationWarning(editorEl, `"${rawInput}" no es válido`);
    cell.value = '';
    setTimeout(() => cell.focus(), 10);  // keep cursor
    return false;
  }

  if (selectedTokens.has(parsed.token)) {
    showValidationWarning(editorEl, `"${parsed.token}" duplicado`);
    cell.value = '';
    return false;
  }

  if (parsed.warning) {
    showValidationWarning(editorEl, parsed.warning);
  }

  selectedTokens.add(parsed.token);
  syncAndRender();
  return true;
}
```

Missatges estàndard:
- `"X" no es válido` — format invàlid.
- `"X" duplicado` — ja existeix.
- `Corregido: orig→fixed` — normalització.
- `Reposicionando pulsos` — nou token entre existents.
- `iT máximo: N` — valor sobre el límit.
- `iT debe ser ≥ 1` — sota el límit.

El `showValidationWarning` mostra el missatge en una bombolla flotant que desapareix automàticament. Comparat amb tooltips custom, té display unificat amb la resta del Lab.

```javascript
let entries = [];        // [{note, temporalInterval, isRest}, ...]
const MAX_TOTAL = 12;    // suma màxima d'iT

function initZigzagEditor(container) {
  // Build static structure
  const wrapper = document.createElement('div');
  wrapper.className = 'nit-editor-wrapper';

  // Row N (notes, rosa)
  const nBar = document.createElement('div');
  nBar.className = 'nit-editor-bar n-bar';
  const nLabel = document.createElement('div');
  nLabel.className = 'nit-editor-label n-label';
  nLabel.textContent = 'N';
  const nCells = document.createElement('div');
  nCells.className = 'nit-editor-cells n-cells';
  nBar.append(nLabel, nCells);

  // Row iT (durations, groc)
  const itBar = document.createElement('div');
  itBar.className = 'nit-editor-bar it-bar';
  const itLabel = document.createElement('div');
  itLabel.className = 'nit-editor-label it-label';
  itLabel.textContent = 'iT';
  const itCells = document.createElement('div');
  itCells.className = 'nit-editor-cells it-cells';
  itBar.append(itLabel, itCells);

  wrapper.append(nBar, itBar);
  container.appendChild(wrapper);

  renderCells({ nCells, itCells });
  return { setPairs, clear, clearHighlights, destroy };

  function renderCells({ nCells, itCells }) {
    nCells.innerHTML = '';
    itCells.innerHTML = '';
    entries.forEach((entry, idx) => {
      // N cell
      const nCell = document.createElement('input');
      nCell.className = 'nit-editor-cell n-cell';
      nCell.value = entry.isRest ? 'S' : entry.note;
      nCell.addEventListener('blur', () => commitN(idx, nCell.value));
      nCells.appendChild(nCell);

      // iT cell
      const itCell = document.createElement('input');
      itCell.className = 'nit-editor-cell it-cell';
      itCell.value = entry.temporalInterval;
      itCell.addEventListener('blur', () => commitIt(idx, itCell.value));
      itCells.appendChild(itCell);
    });

    // Active input cells (per al següent token)
    if (totalSum() < MAX_TOTAL) {
      const nInput = document.createElement('input');
      nInput.className = 'nit-editor-cell n-cell active-input';
      nInput.placeholder = ' ';
      nCells.appendChild(nInput);
      const itInput = document.createElement('input');
      itInput.className = 'nit-editor-cell it-cell active-input';
      itInput.placeholder = ' ';
      itCells.appendChild(itInput);
      // ... event listeners per commit
    }
  }

  function totalSum() {
    return entries.reduce((s, e) => s + e.temporalInterval, 0);
  }
}
```

Editor zigzag amb dues files: N (notes 0-11 o 'S' per silenci) i iT (durada 1-N). Quan l'usuari completa una iT, es commiteja l'entry i s'afegeix una nova active-input.

Look at the configuration you pass to `createFractionEditor`, not at runtime. Each app commits to one variant.

Simple variant config:

```javascript
const controller = createFractionEditor({
  defaults: { numerator: 1, denominator: 2 },     // numerator fixed at 1
  enableGhost: false,                              // skip ghost DOM
  startEmpty: false,
  maxDenominator: 8,
  // ...
});
controller.setSimpleMode();                        // numerator readonly
```

Complex variant config:

```javascript
const controller = createFractionEditor({
  defaults: { numerator: 2, denominator: 3 },     // numerator editable
  autoReduce: true,                                // animates reduction
  minNumerator: 2,
  maxNumerator: 6,
  minDenominator: 2,
  maxDenominator: 8,
  // (NO enableGhost: false — ghost is needed)
  // ...
});
controller.setComplexMode();                       // both editable
```

In the `onChange` callback, you don't need to differentiate — `controller.getFraction()` returns `{numerator, denominator}` in both cases:

```javascript
function handleFractionChange({ cause }) {
  if (cause === 'init') return;
  const f = controller.getFraction();
  if (!Number.isFinite(f.numerator) || !Number.isFinite(f.denominator)) return;
  // For simple, f.numerator is always 1. For complex, it varies.
  currentNumerator = f.numerator;
  currentDenominator = f.denominator;
  if (currentNumerator > 1) {
    // Complex math: (colIdx * n) % d === 0, ghost-pulse-lines, etc.
  }
  renderTimeline();
}
```

For a complex fraction `n/d`, each grid cell represents `n/d` pulses (not `1/d` like in simple fractions). Integer pulses occur where `(colIdx * n) % d === 0`.

Apply the formula in THREE places:

1. **Timeline rendering** (decide if pulse-number or subdivision):

```javascript
for (let colIdx = 0; colIdx < columns; colIdx++) {
  const positionNumerator = colIdx * n;
  const isIntegerPulse = positionNumerator % d === 0;
  const pulseIndex = positionNumerator / d;  // only meaningful when integer
  // ...
}
```

2. **Pulse-boundary class on matrix cells**:

```javascript
const cells = gridElements.matrixContainer.querySelectorAll('.plano-cell');
cells.forEach(cell => {
  const colIndex = parseInt(cell.dataset.colIndex, 10);
  if ((colIndex * n) % d === 0) cell.classList.add('pulse-boundary');
});
```

3. **Pulse highlight during playback**:

```javascript
function highlightPulse(cellIndex) {
  if ((cellIndex * n) % d !== 0) return;  // not an integer pulse
  const pulseIndex = (cellIndex * n) / d;
  // highlight integer pulse...
}
```

For `n=1` (simple variant), all three formulas reduce to `colIdx % d === 0` automatically — same code works for both.

Also adapt **note-bar position calculations** (the bars are positioned by `startSubdiv` which is in scaled units):

```javascript
const startPos = (noteData.startSubdiv * n) / d;
const endPos = ((noteData.startSubdiv + noteData.duration) * n) / d;
```

