In `index.html` keep `randomMenuContent: ''` — `setupRandomMenu` injects the HTML of the inputs into `#randomMenu` after the `.random-menu-title` heading.

The `spec` is a map of `paramName → { label, min, max, default }`. The user can lower defaults via the menu but never exceed them; always clamp with `Math.min(menuValue, HARD_MAX)` inside the handler. Every Nuzic app with parameters must include this — it's a structural feature.

