const MAX_NUMERATOR = 6;
const MAX_DENOMINATOR = 8;
const MIN_REG = 0;
const MAX_REG = 7;
const MAX_NOTES = 16;

const randomMenu = setupRandomMenu({
  spec: {
    numMax:   { label: 'Numerador máximo',   min: 1, max: MAX_NUMERATOR,   default: MAX_NUMERATOR },
    denomMax: { label: 'Denominador máximo', min: 2, max: MAX_DENOMINATOR, default: MAX_DENOMINATOR },
    regMin:   { label: 'Registro mínimo',    min: MIN_REG, max: MAX_REG,  default: MIN_REG },
    regMax:   { label: 'Registro máximo',    min: MIN_REG, max: MAX_REG,  default: MAX_REG },
    notes:    { label: 'Número de notas',    min: 1, max: MAX_NOTES,     default: 8 },
  },
  onRandomize: handleRandom,
});
```

The composition rule: every interactive parameter of the app gets its own entry in the spec. The user can narrow any axis independently — e.g. "only show me examples with denominator ≤ 4 and registers 2-5". Cross-validate paired params (`regMin ≤ regMax`, `bpmMin ≤ bpmMax`) inside the handler with `Math.min`/`Math.max`.

